                <h2 class="text-2xl text-violet-950 mb-5">What is a medical device as per IMDR<span class="text-base"> - "Medical device" refers to:</span></h2>
                <ul class="text-base text-violet-950 mt-3 ml-5">
                    <li class="mb-2">(A) materials used for in vitro diagnostic procedures.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2">(B) materials, including mechanical contraceptives (condoms, intrauterine devices, tubal rings);</li>
                    <li class="mb-2">(C) materials periodically notified under subclause (iv) of clause (b) of section 3 of the Act;</li>
                    <li>(D) materials used for surgical dressings, bandages, staples, sutures, ligatures, and blood and blood component collection bags with or without anticoagulant covered under subclause (i);</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="mb-10">
                <h2 class="text-2xl text-violet-950 mb-5">Medical device classification</h2>
                <p class="text-base text-violet-950 ml-5">Medical device risk is classified into four categories by the Central Licencing Authority (CLA) of India based on the device's intended use, associated risks, and other factors mentioned in the IMDR.</p>
                <ul class="text-base mb-5 text-violet-950 mt-3 ml-5">
                    <li class="mb-2">1. Low risk-Class A</li>
                    <li class="mb-2">2. Low, moderate risk-Class B</li>
                    <li class="mb-2">3. Moderate high risk-Class C</li>
                    <li>4. High risk-Class D</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="ml-5">
                    <h3 class="text-xl text-violet-950">The following guidelines form the basis of how medical devices are categorized:</h3>
                    <ul class="text-base text-violet-950 mt-3 ml-10">
                        <li class="mb-2 list-disc">  The device's intended use will determine the application of classification.</li>
                        <li class="mb-2 list-disc"> Combination items or add-ons should be categorized individually</li>
                        <li class="mb-2 list-disc"> Software should be classified under the same heading as its connected device.</li>
                        <li class="mb-2 list-disc"> Multiple-purpose devices should be categorized according to their most important use.</li>
                        <li> Stricter rules that lead to a higher classification should be applied if multiple rules apply.</li>
                    </ul>
